    "r EDITORIAL PAGE OF THE WASHINGTON TIMES WASHINGTON I C OCTOBER 31 1922 TUESDAY OCTOBER 31 1922 r Once You Could Pay Cash for Killing John Buckley of San Francisco killed a fouryearold girl driving it is alleged while intoxicated He offers to make amends by giving his fiveyerold daughter Isabel to the parents of the dead child and his wife consents to the gift if it will settle the matter It wont in this age and Mr Buckley must stand trial for manslaughter Once that offer would have seemed reasonable in that once not so long ago you could commit a Bran T and settle for cash with the relatives of the dead man The Vi amber of Commerce of the United States lets a buildup contract for two and a half millions specifying opin raop The Chamber of Commerce would get rid of hbor if it could but it cant If it could and did it Would suon be offering many times two and a half millions to bring union labor back again Freedom to work so much talked about is one thing The stabilizing value of well organised unions is another thing much greater more im portant"
